The paper focuses on scene text recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Attention models, which falls under the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Text Mining (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning, falling under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard benchmarks, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
